## Findings Summary

### 1. **Capacity Unit Text** — [templates/store_detail.html](templates/store_detail.html#L24)

**Line 24:** Hardcoded "m²" unit suffix directly in template
```html
{{ store.capacity.value if store and store.capacity and store.capacity.value else '-' }} m²
```
Rendered as: `value m²` (e.g., "1500 m²")

---

### 2. **Country Code/Flag Duplication** — [templates/stores.html](templates/stores.html#L44-L45)

**Lines 44-45:** Country cell displays both flag emoji and raw country code

```html
<span class="flag-emoji" data-country="{{ store.address.value.addressCountry if store and store.address and store.address.value and store.address.value.addressCountry else 'XX' }}"></span>
{{ store.address.value.addressCountry if store and store.address and store.address.value and store.address.value.addressCountry else '-' }}
```

**Issue:** Both the flag emoji span (populated by JS function) AND the text country code render in the same cell, creating duplication.

**CSS for this cell** — [templates/stores.html](templates/stores.html#L150-L157):
```css
.country-cell {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    width: 80px;
}

.flag-emoji {
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
}
```

**JS dependency** — [static/main.js](static/main.js#L2097-L2099):
```javascript
document.querySelectorAll('.flag-emoji[data-country]').forEach((el) => {
    const code = el.getAttribute('data-country');
    el.textContent = countryCodeToEmoji[code] || '🏳️';
});
```

With country code map defined at [static/main.js](static/main.js#L2073-L2093) (ES, FR, IT, PT, DE, GB, etc. → emoji flags)

---

### 3. **Location Column Formatting** — [templates/products.html](templates/products.html#L32-L33)

**Lines 32-33:** Simple count with text label

```html
<td class="inventory-cell">{{ product.inventory_count }} <span data-i18n="table.locations_count">ubicaciones</span></td>
```

Rendered as: `count ubicaciones` (e.g., "3 ubicaciones")

**CSS styling** — [templates/products.html](templates/products.html#L77-L79):
```css
.inventory-cell {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
}
```

No JS dependencies; pure template rendering with i18n label.

